# Keeps agents/ in git so the image build's `COPY agents/ ./agents/`
# (Dockerfile:109) has a directory to copy.
#
# Until SAN-464 the only tracked files here were four auth-state.json — live
# runtime state the container rewrites every boot, tracked by mistake. Untracking
# them emptied agents/ out of git entirely and broke the image build for v1.7.3:
# the build context comes from a clean git checkout, where an empty dir does not
# exist. It went unnoticed because the image is only built on `release: published`,
# never on a PR, and staging builds from source on the VPS where agents/ is on disk.
#
# Ship the directory, not its contents: per-install agent state belongs to the
# install, not to the image.
